 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uveladorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veladorn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/26/01 9:23:54 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://yourpage.blazenet.net/anabelle/triad/valas3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poll: Would you trade it for a Scepter of Al'Kabor</span><hr size=1> Epic is really more then just 800hps, you can click it over for another 800hps and yet another 800hps.  Also, many of the high level mobs have unresistable AE procs.  Ok, I don't know for sure that its unresistable, but it seems like no matter how high your resists are, you still get hit often enough that you have to refresh your epic.<br>
<br>
Epic saves healers mana.<br>
<br>
Staff will give Wizard more mana.<br>
<br>
My feeling is that for raids, epic is better, cleric mana is more important then wizard mana because if tanks start to drop, the raid is lost.  Sometimes my guild even does raids where we tell everyone up front, unless your a warlord, your not getting healed so don't aggro.  Epic is huge again for this because you always get hit, even if its just by AE.  Epic can make a difference if you live or die.<br>
<br>
For day to day grouping or soloing, the Alkabor staff would be better. <p><center><img src=http://yourpage.blazenet.net/anabelle/triad/valas6.jpg hieght=270 width=216></center><BR>
